# Parameters for pointing this container's `claude` at this repo's own
# llm-gateways LiteLLM service instead of api.anthropic.com directly. Read
# by scripts/point-to-gateway.sh (or its "Point Claude CLI at a Gateway"
# menu entry) — see the README's "Pointing Claude CLI at a Gateway"
# section before using this. NOT this environment's own .env — kept
# separate so switching gateways, or reverting, never has to hand-edit or
# lose track of the other gateway's own settings.
#
# host.docker.internal, not a container name or "localhost": claude-cli
# and llm-gateways are two separate Compose projects with no shared
# Docker network, so the only way this container reaches LiteLLM's
# published port is through the host itself — same reasoning llm-gateways'
# own README gives for why LiteLLM reaches Ollama the same way. Match the
# port to whatever LITELLM_PORT actually is in
# environments/llm-gateways/.env (default 4000) if you changed it there.
#
# NOT independently verified against a live LiteLLM instance from inside
# this repo. LiteLLM documents an Anthropic-Messages-API-compatible
# /v1/messages endpoint on this same port (a different request/response
# shape than the /v1/chat/completions OpenAI-format endpoint the rest of
# llm-gateways' own README talks about) — that's what Claude Code's
# ANTHROPIC_BASE_URL actually needs. Confirm your installed LiteLLM
# version still exposes it before relying on this: run
# point-to-gateway.sh, then send `claude` a real message and check it
# actually responds rather than erroring.
ANTHROPIC_BASE_URL=http://host.docker.internal:4000

# LiteLLM's own LITELLM_MASTER_KEY from environments/llm-gateways/.env —
# copy the real value here. This file is never auto-synced with that one.
ANTHROPIC_AUTH_TOKEN=
